	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 23rd 8:51 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would start doing Paludal Caverns around level 18.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get your brass skill max'd out on Denon's Disruptive Discord first and get a handle on instrument twisting.  North Karana is a good place to practice that.  Once comfortable with this effective soloing technique go up to PC and group.  Exp comes fast.  There is no song vendor in Shadow Haven so you may want to buy your 19-25 songs in advance and carry them with you.  Shar Val bard vendors have all the songs but getting there is tricky.  The tunnels are a bit of a maze and its easy to get lost.<br><br>Once you hit 25 do Maru Seru (a lot of folks say Netherbian Lair but I find MS experience is faster with a group).  That will get you to low 30's.  Again, the problem is that you can only buy bard songs in Shar Val or Katta Kastellum; both of which are a pain to get to.  Alternatively, you can port from the Nexus to Greater Feydark or North Karana and run to Kelethin/Qeynos/Freeport to get your songs.  Still a nuisance.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
