<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103529155191675></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103529155191675><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103529155191675>RE: Bard help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103529155191675#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>496 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 22nd 9:18 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 5 the only instrument you need is a lute or mandolin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Either does the same job.  At level 6 get a drum.  You will eventually also need a brass instrument and a wind instrument. Each song that is not sung will need a instrument for best performance (no pun intended).  Some songs won't work at all without the correct instrument. So, you will have 4 different instruments in addition to weapons and armor to fill out your equipment needs.<br><br>Ultimately, the very best string instrument is the Lute of the Howler.  The best drum I am told is Drums of the Beast.<br><br>At level 5 the best place to level is your local newbie zone.  The best place to level varies from level to level. So, I can't really give you a better answer.  You don't mention what city your bard is in now.  Personally, I liked Greater Feydark until level 8.  Then I went by boat to East Commons and West Commons until level 17. Then I went to North Karana &amp; High Hold Pass until level 20.  Spent 2 levels in Paludal Caverns in Luclin.  Just dinged 23 in Maru Seru and Netherbian Lair last nite wtih my bard.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
