	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started soloing my bard at level 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;He is 22 now.  I think I grouped for 4 of those levels.  Currently I am soloing him in LOIO.<br><br>For songs at level 9 mem all but Lyssa's Locating Lyric.  The only 3 I really used was Jonathan's Whistling War Song, Hymn of Restoration, and Selo's Accelerando.  I melee'd with weapon in main hand and shield in other. No instruments except during down time.  When I got dual weild skill I sold the shield and use another weapon. Now, at 22 I use mostly instrument twisting instead of weapons.<br><br>My strategy was to pick a target. If it con'd blue and was not likely to pull adds I would attack it.<br><br>I saved all the spiderling silks and LQ, MQ, and HQ pelts I could find.  Then traded them (about 5 stacks of spiderling silks, 5 stacks spider silks, 2 of the LQ and MQ and a few HQ hides) to a tailor/smith along with 100pp for a set of Fine Steel Plate armor. Found some nice, affordable weapons by merchant farming.  Also, at level 11 I started doing Willowisps.  I took the greater lightstones (backpacks full) to North Karana and traded them to a gypsy for Concordance of Research. Then sold the concordence back to her for 8.5 pp each.  All the gear he has now was farmed or bought from vendors or players (with the exception of a gift of Mistmoore Battle Drums).<br><br>Do the newbie armor quests if you haven't already.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
