<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103306252293819></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103306252293819><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103306252293819>RE: Targets</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103306252293819#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>496 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 26th 2:04 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>1) it depends on the song.&nbsp;&nbsp;If its AoE then it does not matter what you have targeted. If the creature is in range it will be affected - whether you want it to be or not.  If the song is single target only then you must have that creature targeted for the song to take affect.<br><br>2) primary only means you can only equip it in the primary melee slot and not the secondary (or off-hand) slot.  It does not stop you from equipping another weapon in your secondary slot (unless its a 2 handed weapon).<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
