<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103287950581989></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103287950581989><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103287950581989>Chant / Charm Kiiting configuration!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103287950581989#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=173421><span id= >Quasare</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>24 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 24th 11:14 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.96]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greating Bards!<br>Here is the best way (for me...of course p) to chant / charm kit mobs :)<br><br>Open a new Hotkey slot (ex: shift+2)<br>in 1 : Selo accelerating chorus song 49<br>in 2 : Tuyen chant of flame song 38<br>in 3 : Fulfil curt chant song 30<br>in 4 : Tuyen chant of frost song 46<br>in 5 : Solon bewithching bravura song 39<br>in 6 : Largo absonant binding song 51<br>in 7 : Pet attack (create a &quot;/pet attack&quot; hotkey) <br>8, 9 et 10 : what you want ( you can put Hymn of resto or catana of replish (55) in one of them)<br><br>Here is a link where you can see how it will look like: www.chez.com/legacyofaggression/bardkitting.htm<br><br>On the song list I mem Selo song of travel and Catana of replishment too.<br><br>CHANT KITING: (put the drum in your hands!! very important as they are percussion songs)<br>- Target the mob<br>- Hit 1<br>- Then hit 4-3-2 (or 2-3-4 lol)<br>Selo makes you run during 2,5 minutes but you can refresh it every 4 or 5 rows of chant...<br>When the mob is low life and alone: he will run away....and this can be veeeerrrryyy bad! :) <br>- then hit 6, so he wont move and cast just 2 songs in a row with 6 (6 is not included)<br>=&gt; and hop XP :) Wooooooot!<br>Don't forget to put a drum in your hand or it will last for hours!! :)<br><br>CHARM KITING:<br>(Here it becomes funny ;))<br>- Hit 1<br>- Make a train (yes yes a train! :) with at least if you can 4 or more mobs running to bite your ass...try with green ones first for testing)<br>- Target 1 mob (try to take the highest lvl if there are differences between them)<br>- Hit 5 (mob charmed)<br>- turn and face your train and hit F8 (it will target the nearest mob to you and your pet is not considered as a mob)<br>- Hit 7 (I press it many time just to be sure :) )<br>And hop.....magic p!<br>- Hit &quot;2 TIMES!!&quot; F1 (first time: you, then second: your pet) to target your pet again :)<br>Verant just change the duration of the charm song now: from 18 secondes to 1 minutes or so....charm is a little different now...<br>If it is going too slow for you, you can help your pet with chant kit (/assist),&nbsp;&nbsp;but your pet will loose less hp...<br>- When your pet only stand at least, kill him with chant kit! :)<br>=&gt; Crazzzzzzzzyyyyyy XP!!!! :)<br><br>I hope it helps!<br>Good luck to you all bards!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Oct 16 10:04:54 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Valaba Noirac<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150528" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150528</a></td></tr>
