<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103217908635054></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103217908635054><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103217908635054>RE: hotkey or something?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103217908635054#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>496 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 16th 8:39 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>What I do for hotkey:<br><br>First have 4 open hot key slots on you hotkey pad. Make sure they are adjacent (I find its easier).&nbsp;&nbsp;Next, open your inventory window.  Left click on your primary melee slot and hold the mouse button down.  A copy of the melee slot will hop onto your mouse cursor.  You can let up on the button now.  Drag the melee slot icon to the first empty hotkey slot and left click. The melee slot copy drops in.  Repeat for secondary melee slot and two open inventory slots.  You can now swap weapons into the inventory slot by just picking them up normally with the mouse cursor and dropping them into the available hotkey slot. Note that most instruments are 2 handed, secondary melee slot only. So, you cannot equip most weapons with most instruments (there are a few exceptions).<br><br>Song twisting is busy work.  It requires focus.  Sounds like you have the right idea. With practice you should be able to do 3 songs easily. 4 with difficulty (and a very reliable internet connection).  Internet latency is a bards biggest enemy - more so than Nagafen, Vox or any of the Planes.<br><br>I suggest you set up a series of hot keys for you 3 most commonly used songs.  I have 5 keys on my 1st keypad screen.  Just as above, left click on the spell gem for the song and hold down the mouse button till a copy of the icon appears on your cursor.  Drop it onto an empty hotkey slot.  You can use the number keys at the top of your keyboard to activate the song in the hotkey slot. Much faster and easier to coordinate than using a mouse.  My set up for soloing at level 22 has hotkeys like this:<br><br>Jon. Whist War Song      Hymn of Restoration<br>Brucoes Boast. Bellow    Largo's Mel. Binding<br>Selo's Accelerando       misc key (usually assist)<br>Primary Melee            Secondary Melee<br>Inventory Slot 3         Inventory Slot 4<br><br>I keep my weapons in primary and secondary melee slots.  I keep my mandolin or my drums in inventory 4 and leave inventory 3 open for swapping out my primary melee weapon.  When swapping to an instrument I use the mouse to move my primary melee out first. Then exchange my secondary melee for my instrumtent in inventory slot 4.  Alternatively, I may not use weapons at all but will switch my mandolin and my horn back and forth and put Denon's Disruptive Discord into Hotkey slot 6.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
