<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103217896635067></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103217896635067><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103217896635067>RE: hotkey or something?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103217896635067#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87819><span id=Sage>iteck</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>104 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 16th 8:37 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, this is the way I do it (there are probably loads of other ways too):<br><br>On your hotkeys pad map keys 2 = primary weapon slot, 4 = inventory slot number 8, 6 = secondary weapon slot. <br>Place you instrument in your inventory slot number 8 and have your weapons/weapons + shield in your primary and secondary weapon slots.<br>Now when you want to swap weapons to instrument you do the following:<br>a. Click on hotkey 2 (you have now picked up your main weapon on your cursor and your main weapon slot is empty).<br>b. Click on hotkey 4 (you have now swapped your main weapon with your instrument so you main weapon is now in inventory slot 8, and you instrument is on your cursor).<br>c. Click on hotkey 6 (you have now swapped your instrument with your secondary weapon/shield, so you now have your instrument in your secondary slot and you have your secondary weapon on your cursor).<br>d. Optional, put secondary weapon in a bag or another free inventory slot.<br>To swap back you do it all in reverse:<br>a. If it's not on your cursor then pick up your secondary weapon.<br>b. Click on hotkey 6 (swap secondary weapon with instrument).<br>c. Click on hotkey 4 (swap instrument with main weapon in inventory slot 8).<br>d. Click on hotkey 2 (put weapon in main weapon slot).<br>Using this setup I can swap weapons and instruments	 in less than  a second (lag permitting).<br><br>One thing to note is this method really requires you to turn off 'inspect others' and 'trade with others' because (especially if you don't bother to put your secondary weapon away) there is nothing worse than having to cancel a mistaken trade halfway through a battle.<br><br>With the new UI things have got even better.&nbsp;&nbsp;With a small amount of playing with the XML for my hot buttons, I now have my main and secondary weapon slots and my inventory slot 8 all on my hot buttons bar, thus freeing up 3 hotkey keys (I can post the bits if anybody wants it).  The new UI also allows you  to have leave bags open so I now keep one bad open off to one side so I can put my off hand weapon down if I want, along with the opportunity quickly swap out instruments.<br><br>As to your other point:<br><br>There are loads of guides to twisting and a lot more experienced bards on this board who can probably explain this better but:<br>a. Start first song.<br>b. As soon as you see first song start (your casting bar finishes), stop first song and start second song by double clicking on second song icon.<br>c. As soon as you see second song start (your casting bar finishes), stop second song and start third song by double clicking on third song icon.<br>d. As soon as you see third song start (your casting bar finishes), stop third song and start first song by double clicking on first song icon.<br>If you get this right then congratulations you are now twisting three songs.  As you get higher you get some songs that last longer than the usual 3 ticks (amplification being one of the main ones) and so you can start doing four or more song twists.  If you want to set up some hotkeys to do a bit of work then a (very) simple one would look something like this:<br>/stopsong<br>/cast 1<br><br>If you are feeling really masochistic then you can do all of the above, twisting songs and weapons, but I wouldn't recommend it <img src=/ubbnew/graemlins/grin.gif><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
