<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103157633496893></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103157633496893><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103157633496893>RE: Undecided</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103157633496893#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>496 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 9th 9:13 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards can solo effectively even into the highest levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;But it takes patience.  My guess is you have done some bow kiting with your ranger by now.  Kiting with a bard is different tactic but takes time.  Bards are great because they are versitile. Jack of all trades - master of none.  You can be a tank. You will not be as good at it as a warrior.  You can be healer. You will not be as good at it as a cleric.  You can charm, fear, boost mana regen.  But you will never be as good at it as an Enchanter. So long as you use all these roles together, with forthought and patience, you can solo a bard quite well.  A bard that makes mistakes on balancing these roles is a dead bard.  A bard is a thinking persons class. It requires constant attention to the situation at hand.  You need superior judgement and timing to know when to switch songs, insturments, and weapons.  It is perhaps the most complicated class to play.  You will never, ever, find yourself without anything to do.  If you like to do a lot of chatting you will find little time for that while playing a bard.<br><br>Honestly, the most fun I have as a bard is out on the plains of Karana or LOIO when I can race past that druid 10 levels higher than me, shouting, &quot;Meep! Meep!&quot;  Oh, what a wonderful feeling!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
