<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103157668596949></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103157668596949><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103157668596949>RE: NeW</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=103157668596949#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>496 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 9th 9:19 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Based on what I have seen half-elf is very popular.&nbsp;&nbsp;Personally, I went with Vah Shir. Sometimes bards have to melee and the cats have good stats in that area.  Since bards are a plate class the extra STR doesnt hurt.  I have seen a lot of wood elf bards, too.  The DEX from the elven types is very useful to a bard.  It helps prevent missed notes. Kitty DEX is good too.  Bards need mana for some songs at higher levels. So, INT doesnt hurt. But I would emphasize STR, DEX, and CHA.  CHA is real helpful with charm songs at higher levels.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
