	   <tr><td colspan=2>AC and AGI would help.&nbsp;&nbsp;You don't say what tactics you are using. So its hard to recommend gear. I spent much of my upper teens in the Karanas but never had a beetle bash me before.  That must be new. At that level I melee'd a lot but I had some decent weapons and a full suit of Fine Steel Plate.  I mainly played JWW,Bruco's, HoR, and SA. Soloed most of the way to 20.  <br><br>No it was not twinkage.  I farmed a lot of spiderling silk, LQ pelts, and greater lightstones.  I gave the silk and pelts to a tailor/smith friend along will all the plat from the lightstones. She made me the armor so she could skill up. The weapons I found in Felwithe where someone had dumped them on a vendor and I bought back cheap.<br><br>So, if you have lambent or better already my suggestion won't help much. But if you are still mostly in leather/banded armor I suggest you try my route and find a friendly smith/tailor.<br><br>DEX, BTW, decreases your chance of missed notes. I don't think it will keep your songs from being interrupted.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
